3380	\begin{proof}
3381	  \uses{def:basis_cov_system}
3382	  An epimorphism in an abelian category is characterised by vanishing cokernel. The underlying
3383	  abelian-sheaf functor on sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules is additive and exact (it preserves
3384	  finite colimits, being a left adjoint composed with the exact sheafification–forgetful comparison),
3385	  so it sends the cokernel of \(g\) to the cokernel of the image of \(g\); since the former is zero,
3386	  so is the latter, and the image of \(g\) is an epimorphism.
3387	\end{proof}
